It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) because the paper deals with generating adversarial images that look more realistic to human eyes. 

Furthermore, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because the paper proposes a new approach to adversarial attacks that uses a generative model. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because the paper deals with adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in security research. 

Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because the paper uses neural networks, specifically GANs, to generate adversarial examples.
